abstract.value: The Food Studies Ephemera Collection consists of pamphlets, recipe booklets, and other food- and cookery-related ephemera donated to Fales by various donors.

p.value: Identification of item, date; Food Studies Ephemera Collection; MSS 310; box number; folder number or item identifier; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University.
Materials gifted by various donors from 2011 to 2019. The accession numbers associated with this collection are 2011.310, 2014.412, 2015.310, 2018.094, and 2019.051.

The Food Studies Ephemera Collection consists of printed ephemera (primarily pamphlets and recipe booklets) having to do with food and cookery. The bulk of the materials are from the mid-twentieth century.

subject.value: Food industry and trade -- United States.
